column5: another 10mm forecast for lindsay and surrounding area's already seems everything close to bursting with high water levels, happy i am 20 ft above the lake right now as my concrete dock is under water and don't even know where the wooden one went and it was tied to the railway.

Peterboro news was saying it's expected the Ottonabee River flowing towards Rice Lake will rise 1/2 a metre over the next few days so that could cause some serious problems for the waterfront homes.  Last thing anyone needs is this rain that's coming today.
last year no water this year is nuts
